author: wn.com
title: Portman slams Strickland for calling him his “enemy”
text: Sen. Rob Portman criticized Democratic Senate candidate Ted Strickland for calling him “our enemy” in a speech the former Democratic governor delivered earlier this week to Democrats in Cincinnati. “I don’t think that you can be an effective senator if you think that the other party is your enemy,” Portman told reporters Thursday on a conference call. “That’s part of the problem why Washington doesn’t work.”
